 \">Refs</a>]: <i>pluperfect</i> ἐκέχρηστο (variant{ἐκέχρητο}) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.147, 151, 3.64, etc.\">Refs</a>]:—<i>middle</i>, χρῶμαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.126, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>Ionic dialect</i> χρέομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>], <i>infinitive</i> χρέεσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1.157 (χρᾶσθαι [prev. work] 172)\">Refs</a>]; <i>participle</i> χρεώμενος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.151: \">Refs</a>]<i>imperfect</i> <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>plural</i> ἐχρέωντο (variant{ἐχρέοντο}) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4.157, 5.82 \">Refs</a>]: <i>future</i> χρήσομαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.492, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.I</b></Level2> in <i>active</i> of the gods and their oracles, <b>proclaim,</b> <i>absolutely</i>, χρείων μυθήσατο Φοῖβος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8.79: χρείων ἐκ δάφνης γυάλων ὕπο Παρνησοῖο “hymnus ad Apollinem” 396: with _accusative_ _of things_, χρήσω ἀνθρώποισι Διὸς βουλήν [prev. work] 132, compare 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 807, Pi.[same place], 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 2.9.9; ἡ Πυθίη οἱ χρᾷ τάδε 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.55, compare 4.155 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; χρῆσεν οἰκιστῆρα Βάττον <b>proclaimed</b> him the colonizer, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also in Trag., ὁ χρήσας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 798; χρήσειν ἔοικεν ἀμφὶ τῶν αὑτῆς κακῶν [prev. author] “Ag.” 1083; χρῇ μοι τοιαῦθ᾽ ὁ Φοῖβος 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 35; σοὶ δ᾽ οὐκ ἔχρησεν οὐδέν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 1268; χ. φόνον [prev. author] “El.” 1267: also with _accusative_ _cognate_, χ. χρησμόν [prev. author] “Ph.” 409; ὑμνῳδίαν [prev. author] “Ion” 681 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: with <i>infinitive</i>, <b>warn</b> or <b>direct by oracle,</b> ἔχρησας ὥστε τὸν ξένον μητροκτονεῖν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 202; without ὥστε, [prev. work] 203 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; χρήσαντ᾽ ἐμοὶ.. ἐκτὸς αἰτίας κακῆς εἶναι <b>that</b> I should be.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ch.” 1030 \">Refs</a>]; with <i>infinitive</i> <i>aorist</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 159 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: rare in <i>Attic dialect</i> Prose, τάδε ὁ Ἀπόλλων ἔχρησεν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12.80.10; τὸν Ἀπόλλω ταύτην τὴν γῆν χρῆσαι οἰκεῖν 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.102; τοῦ θεοῦ χρήσαντος [prev. author] 5.32, compare 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 99; ἔχρησεν ὁ θεός “SIG” 1044.5 (Halic., 4th-3rd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὁ θεὸς ἔχρησε [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 42(1).122.78 (Epid., 4th c.BC). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.II</b></Level2> <i>passive</i>, <b>to be declared, proclaimed</b> by an oracle, τίς οὖν ἐχρήσθ; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 792 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; mostly of the <b>oracle delivered,</b> τὰ ἐκ Δελφῶν οὕτω τῷ Κροίσῳ ἐχρήσθη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.49; τὰ χρηστήρια ταῦτά σφι ἐχρήσθη [prev. author] 9.94; ἠπίως χρησθῆναι [prev. author] 7.143 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ χρησθέν, τὰ χρησθέντα, the <b>response,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.63, 7.178; ἐν Πυθῶνι χρησθὲν παλαίφατον 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 2.39; πεύθου τὰ χρησθέντ᾽ 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 604 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χρησθὲν αὐτῷ ἐν Νεμέᾳ τοῦτο παθεῖν <b>since it was foretold</b> him <b>by an oracle</b> that.. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.96 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἃ τοῦδ᾽ ἐχρήσθη σώματος which <b>were declared</b> about it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 355; τὸν κεχρησμένον θάνατον 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.164 (-χρημ- codices)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τοῦ κακοῦ τοῦ κεχρησμένου [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 7.141 (variant{-χρημ-}): _impersonal_, with \">Refs</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, καί σφι ἐχρήσθη ἀνέμοισι εὔχεσθαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 178 \">Refs</a>]: with <i>accusative</i> et <i>infinitive</i>, ἐκέχρηστό σφι.. τοῦτον βασιλεύσειν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 2.147 \">Refs</a>]; with <i>infinitive</i> <i>aorist</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 7.220. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__B.III</b></Level2> <i>middle</i>, of the person to whom the response is given, <b>consult a god</b> or <b>oracle,</b> with <i>dative</i>, ψυχῇ χρησόμενος Θηβαίου Τειρεσίαο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 10.492, 565 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χ. θεῷ, χρηστηρίοισι, μαντηΐῳ, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.47, 53, 157; τῷ θεῷ 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 3.124; χ. μάντεσι Μούσαις 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 724 (_anapaest meter_), compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 686a; ὅσοι μαντικὴν νομίζοντες οἰωνοῖς χρῶνται 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 1.1.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. χρηστηρίῳ εἰ.. <b>inquire at</b> the oracle whether.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.57: _absolutely_, ὑπέρβη λάϊνον οὐδὸν χρησόμενος 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.81, compare “hymnus ad Apollinem” 252, 292; ἀπέστειλε ἄλλους χρησομένους 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.46 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; οἱ χρώμενοι the <b>consulters,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 957; χρωμένῳ ἐν Δελφοῖς 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 1.126; also χ. περὶ τοῦ πολέμου 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.220, compare 1.85, 4.150, 155, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κεχρημένος <b>having inquired of an oracle,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1398b33: with \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<i>infinitive</i>, σωφρονεῖν κεχρημένον <b>being divinely warned</b> to be temperate, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 829, compare 4th c.AD(?): Marcellinus Biographus “Vita Thucydidis” 6 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: later simply, <b>receive a divine revelation,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 5.3.14.— 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] has the word in this sense only in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey”: the \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<i>active</i> only in <i>present</i> <i>participle</i> χρείων (<i>future</i> χρήσω [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Apollinem” 132): the \">Refs</a>]<i>middle</i> only in <i>participle</i> <i>future</i> χρησόμενος. <br /><Level1><b>__B</b></Level1> <b>furnish with</b> a thing, in which sense the <i>present</i> was <b>κίχρημι</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 53.12, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Pompeius” 29 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; Cretan dialect <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>singular</i> κίγχρητι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Inscription Cretan dialect” 1 xxiii 3 (Phaestus, 2nd c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; Delph. <i>3rd.pers.</i> <i>singular</i> <i>present</i> <i>subjunctive</i> κιχρῇ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Schwyzer” 324.17 (4th c.BC): \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<i>aorist</i> χρέη[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work]13\">Refs</a>]; <i>present</i> <i>participle</i> κιχρέντε [<a href=\"javascript: